description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Practice Development Nurse within the Neonatal Services at Peterborough City Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about clinical education and supporting and developing newly appointed staff, post registered and pre-registered nurses?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be need to be highly motivated, a skilled practitioner, professional role model and communicator. You should be comfortable teaching in a group situation as well as 1:1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working clinically with pre-registration, newly qualified nurses or nurses new to the Trust or to acute care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitating clinical and educational programmes for a variety of learners in classroom and clinical settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and supporting preceptors and mentors to adhere to the Trust and national guidelines giving appropriate guidance where required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in collaboration with Clinical Nurse Educators and senior nursing teams to ensure a supportive learning environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracy James - Lead Nurse for Neonatal Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tracy.james@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
